    "Summarizing the dataset in natural language and using this as a prompt can help the LLM perform the analysis task more effectively.The data introduction includes a natural language description of the column names of each variable in the data, the types of variables and some statistical indicators.",
    "The given output json format template and some existing descriptions of the data (or not) are passed to LLM as prompts and let it generate data introduction according to the given format.This is an example that we provide for the cars dataset.1 class DataProperty { 2 column: string; // Column Name 3 description: string; // Natural language description 4 dtype: string; // Data type of the column 5 std: number | null; // Standard deviation, null if not applicable 6 samples: string[]; // Sample values from the column 7 nunique: number; // Number of unique values in the column 8 min: string; // Minimum value in the column 9 max: string; // Maximum value in the column 10 } 1 { 2 \"columns\": [ 3 \"Name\", 4 \"Miles per Gallon\", 5 \"Cylinders\", 6 \"Displacement\", 7 \"Horsepower\", 8 \"Weight in lbs\", 9 \"Acceleration\", 10 \"Year\", 11 \"Origin\" 12], 13 \"properties\": [ 14 { 15 \"column\": \"Name\", 16 \"description\": \"The make and model of the car."
